description: Returns the logging status of a bucket and the permissions users have to view and modify that status. The following operations are related to GetBucketLogging:

parameters.name: Bucket
parameters.description: The bucket name for which to get the logging information.

nested_items.name: LoggingEnabled
nested_items.description: Describes where logs are stored and the prefix that Amazon S3 assigns to all log object keys for a bucket. For more information, see PUT Bucket logging in the Amazon S3 API Reference.

nested_items.name: TargetBucket
nested_items.description: Specifies the bucket where you want Amazon S3 to store server access logs. You can have your logs delivered to any bucket that you own, including the same bucket that is being logged. You can also configure multiple buckets to deliver their logs to the same target bucket. In this case, you should choose a different TargetPrefix for each source bucket so that the delivered log files can be distinguished by key.

nested_items.name: ID
nested_items.description: The canonical user ID of the grantee.

nested_items.name: Permission
nested_items.description: Logging permissions assigned to the grantee for the bucket.

nested_items.name: TargetPrefix
nested_items.description: A prefix for all log object keys. If you store log files from multiple Amazon S3 buckets in a single bucket, you can use a prefix to distinguish which log files came from which bucket.

nested_items.name: TargetObjectKeyFormat
nested_items.description: Amazon S3 key format for log objects.

nested_items.name: SimplePrefix
nested_items.description: To use the simple format for S3 keys for log objects. To specify SimplePrefix format, set SimplePrefix to {}.

nested_items.name: PartitionedPrefix
nested_items.description: Partitioned S3 key for log objects.

nested_items.name: PartitionDateSource
nested_items.description: Specifies the partition date source for the partitioned prefix. PartitionDateSource can be EventTime or DeliveryTime.
